    <body>
      <div type="letter">
        <head>
          <title>
            12 June 1762. – Letter from <persName key="p0053" ref="8b70ea75-427b-4d3f-82ea-93a9f1c42b48">Joseph Emin</persName> to <persName key="p0065" ref="c8f0f482-fa7d-4e84-ac52-891dcb4d2adb">the Russian Envoy Extraordinary
            to London / Vice-Chancellor, Prince Aleksandr Mikhailovich Golitsyn</persName>
          </title>
          <note>
            <bibl>RGADA, fond 1263, opis 1, no. 481, f. 1, 2v. English original.</bibl>
          </note>
        </head>
        <pb n="f. 1"/>
        <p/>
        <p>my Noble Prince</p>
        <p>Your Excellency’s great fatigue of journey I hope is long over, and have enjoyed yourself
          among your noble family. Especialy when reflected seriously upon the good administration
          your Excellency did perform with the toils of mind for so many years in the <orgName key="o0002" ref="dd406ffb-30ce-4374-868b-1a55e8daf251">Court of old Britain</orgName>,
          must be an inward happiness not only in your noble mind in the presence of his august <persName key="p0115" ref="e958d8b8-e12f-4ac9-b67f-d19c20fb4dcc">Emperial Majesty Peter the third</persName>
          whom God preserve, but to all your noble relation, to all your friends, and to those who
          are friends to mankind, as for my part in gratitude to your Excellency’s patronage, and
          friendship, I am not able to express my joy or how glad, and happy it has made me when I
          read <persName cert="high" evidence="internal" full="yes" generatedBy="human" instant="unknown" key="p2273" xml:space="default">Doctor Mounsy</persName>’s letter from England wherin [sic] I
          had the information of your Excellency return to your native land. I hope your Excellency
          have left the friends all well in old England, and found the friends at <placeName key="g0002" ref="https://www.geonames.org/498817">St Petersburg</placeName> the same.</p>
        <p> I shall remain here sometime, that <persName key="p0082" ref="c1629e8b-12bd-4f5b-9e53-18ca54f33a83">prince Heraclius</persName> shoud [sic] know
          his fathers death the late <persName cert="high" evidence="internal" full="yes" generatedBy="human" instant="unknown" key="p0137" xml:space="default">Prince Thomraz</persName> before, for
          the sake of our oriental superstition, which is an evil that have ruined many countries,
          he may take a bad liking to me, looking upon it as an ill omen. Princes in the East were
          become a hattred enemy to those of their best friends for a bad news. Therefore I stay
          here, till it becomes little old, and in the meantime if your Excellency have any
          commands, to impose on me, here or elsewhere, I am ready to execute it with the utmost of
          my ability, to show that I have not forgot your Excellency’s labour in recommending to the <persName key="p0145" ref="d2b65a85-e89e-4a89-b0ff-b30a4b529b9c">great Chancellor</persName>, in
          taking pains to foreward my honest designs, and in kind reception in London. I have the
          honor</p>
        <p>my Noble Prince</p>
        <p>your Excellency’s</p>
        <p>most obed<hi rendition="#sup">t</hi>, most obliged,</p>
        <p>and gratefull humble servant</p>
        <p>
          <persName cert="high" evidence="internal" full="yes" generatedBy="human" instant="unknown" key="p0053" xml:space="default" ref="8b70ea75-427b-4d3f-82ea-93a9f1c42b48" type="signature">Emin of the mountaineers
            of Armenia</persName>
        </p>
        <p>
          <placeName key="g0024" ref="https://www.geonames.org/580497">Astrachan</placeName> the 12<hi rendition="#sup">th</hi> June 1762</p>
        <p>at <persName cert="high" evidence="internal" full="yes" generatedBy="human" instant="unknown" key="p2274" xml:space="default">Mr Renttes</persName>, or <persName cert="high" evidence="internal" full="yes" generatedBy="human" instant="unknown" key="p1724" xml:space="default">Nicholaus
          Ivanwich</persName>
        </p>
        <p/>
        <pb n="f.2 v"/>
        <p/>
        <p>
          <placeName key="g0024" ref="https://www.geonames.org/580497">Astrachan</placeName> le 12. Juin 1762</p>
        <p>De <persName key="p0053" ref="8b70ea75-427b-4d3f-82ea-93a9f1c42b48">l’armenien</persName>
        </p>
        <p>
          <persName key="p0053" ref="8b70ea75-427b-4d3f-82ea-93a9f1c42b48">Emin</persName>
        </p>
        <p>To</p>
        <p>
          <persName key="p0065" ref="c8f0f482-fa7d-4e84-ac52-891dcb4d2adb">His Excellency Prince
            Galitzin</persName>
        </p>
        <p>Lately minister at the <orgName key="o0002" ref="dd406ffb-30ce-4374-868b-1a55e8daf251">Court
          of Great Britain</orgName>
        </p>
      </div>
